# TikTok Shop factory code

## Scope

Automation only — **no creative strategy in code**. Course wins for hooks, captions, product pick logic.

Key paths:

- `module1_qc.py` — mandatory pre-upload gate; do not bypass without owner emergency
- `factory_cli.py` — CLI entry: status, scout, render, make-clip, qc, enqueue, post
- `scout_cli.py` / `echotik_client.py` — product research API
- `kling_client.py` / `render.py` — video generation
- `video_variants.py` — pan loop edit
- `poster.py` / `zernio` — upload path
- `queue.py` / `quota.py` — daily cap + post spacing
- `accounts.json` — `affiliate_main` + bubble slots

## Conventions

- Match existing naming, imports, and CLI patterns in `factory_cli.py`
- Minimize diff scope — affiliate pipeline fixes only unless asked
- Tests: `python3 -m pytest tests/ -q` when touching QC or scout logic
- Do not reintroduce dead lanes (Ms. Byte, InVideo, Peripheral) in comments or defaults

## QC

Every upload path must pass `module1_qc.py`. Caption and product name feed posting-rule checks (spacing, duplicate product same day).

## Config

- `affiliate_main.enabled` false until owner wires purchased account
- `KLING_MODE=std` default (~$0.21/5s) unless owner requests pro
- Secrets via Cursor Cloud Agent → `bash scripts/install.sh` — never commit `.env`

